My meme

  • My meme represents what I do for most of my assignments. Pedro Pascal on LSD seems to capture the essence of the meme. Plus Im a big Last of us Mandalorian fan .

library(magick)
#library(magrittr)
pedro_pascal <- image_read("https://i.kym-cdn.com/editorials/icons/mobile/000/005/501/myom1.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(geometry=670)  # reads the image online and scales it.

meme_text <- image_blank(color = "black", width = 670, height = 50) %>% #The text for the meme on a blank image
  image_annotate(text = "Me to my lecturers when they ask me how far I am on an assignment\n (I am startinging 5 hours before the due date)", size = 20, gravity = "north", color = "white")


meme_vector <- c(pedro_pascal,meme_text) 
meme <- image_append(meme_vector, stack=TRUE) # appending the text and the image for the meme
image_write(meme, "my_meme.jpg") # Creating the image chose jpg format, png creates a weird version of the meme for some reason.
meme

My animated GIF

  • Well I am a big fan of cinema, and I thought it would be an amazing idea to make a collection of cinemas most disturbing individuals.

library(magick)
#library(magrittr)
image1 <- image_read("https://www.looper.com/img/gallery/hannibal-lecters-backstory-explained/intro-1568920260.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(400) %>%
    image_annotate(text = "Just sleep tight, they are watching over you !", size = 20, gravity = "north", color = "white")

image2 <- image_read("https://i.insider.com/62c79a7499259b00181e69f9?width=1000&format=jpeg&auto=webp") %>% 
  image_scale(400) %>%
    image_annotate(text = "Just sleep tight, they are watching over you !", size = 20, gravity = "north", color = "white")

image3 <- image_read("https://pyxis.nymag.com/v1/imgs/1d1/c48/b5dc2fd31a225d2944b83f39053fcc2820-11-us-trailer-jordan-peele.rhorizontal.w700.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(400) %>%
    image_annotate(text = "Just sleep tight, they are watching over you !",size = 20, color = "white")

image4 <- image_read("https://sm.askmen.com/askmen_in/topten/a/anton-chig/anton-chigurh-no-country-for-old-men_x5h4.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(400) %>%
    image_annotate(text = "Just sleep tight, they are watching over you !", size = 20, gravity = "north", color = "white")

my_gif <- c(image1,image2,image3,image4) %>%
  image_animate(fps=1)
my_gif %>% image_write("animation.gif")
my_gif
